## Quick Reference: Key Facts to Know Cold

| Statement | Where it comes from |
|---|---|
| $\sum_j q_{ij} = 1$ for all $i$ | Definition of transition matrix |
| $(Q^n)_{ij} = P(X_n = j \mid X_0 = i)$ | $Q^n$ theorem |
| $q_{ij}^{(m+n)} = \sum_k q_{ik}^{(m)} q_{kj}^{(n)}$ | Chapman-Kolmogorov |
| $p^{(n)} = p^{(0)} Q^n$ | Row-vector evolution |
| $\pi Q = \pi$ | Stationary distribution condition |
| $Q^{m+n} = Q^m Q^n$ | Matrix form of Chapman-Kolmogorov |
| $(Q^n)_{ij} \neq (q_{ij})^n$ | Common mistake |
| Markov $\not\Rightarrow$ independent across time | Common mistake |
